The paper focuses on training a single neural network executable at different widths, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves switchable batch normalization, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the performance of the slimmable models across a wide range of applications, including object detection and segmentation, which are common topics in natural language processing (cs.CL).
